 SOPE (SKYRiX Object Publishing Environment) is an extensive set of
 Objective-C frameworks (16 frameworks, ~1500 classes) which form a
 complete Web application server environment. Besides the Apple
 WebObjects compatible appserver that has been extended with Zope
 concepts, it contains a large set of reusable classes: XML processing
 (SAX2, DOM, XML-RPC), MIME/IMAP4 processing, LDAP connectivity, RDBMS
